title: For Sale:  Custom Savage Striker 516 7mm-08 w/ Leupold VX-3 2.5-8x32mm + More
postcontent:
This is a Savage Striker 516 in 7mm-08 caliber.  This is not your average striker, but a customized build to create a great Striker.  The scope is a $450 Leupold VX-3 2.5-8x32mm handgun scope with duplex reticle.  The mounts are Burris Signature 1" rings on a Weaver-style steel full-length base.  Included is a Harris bipod.

What makes it a custom?  I had the OEM stock and scope coated in Realtree Hardwoods HD Brown by Tarjac, one of the best in camo-coating.  But the best feature is the Muscle Brake muzzle brake, installed by Devin at Sin Arms.  This is the Mini-Magnum Muscle Brake, designed by Neal Cooper and purchased from Piercision Rifles.  What makes the Muscle Brake great is the first ports direct the blast sideways away from the shooter.  The 2nd and 3rd ports direct the blast slightly backwards.  So the magic of this muzzle brake is it significantly reduces recoil and muzzle jump, while protecting the shooter from the concussion produced by must muzzle brakes, including the OEM Savage round brake.  The final touch is the trigger has been worked on by Sin Arms.  Devin cleaned up the trigger, significantly reduce the travel (creep) and reduced the spring tension.  The result is a trigger much better and more enjoyable than the stock trigger.

Also included in this purchase is a Doskosil case, the original purchase receipt for the Striker from 2003, the owners manuals, the original box from when it was purchased, and Butler Creek scope covers.  The case has some rust spots on the latches, so don't expect it to be perfect.  It's simply a good older hardcase for transporting the Striker, but nothing fancy.

This is not your average Striker, and I have a lot of money invested in this build.  It is a very sweet shooter.  My price is $1,100 shipped for the entire package.  The only reason to sell it is I am pursuing other interests, namely purchasing a side-by-side UTV.  I have at least 30 photos from every angle, so please write me and I will email additional photos to you.  I will only ship to an FFL.  Payment must by via US Postal money order (it will take two of them since the max for USPS is $1,000 per money order).  Please ensure you can own this firearm in your state.  It is classified by ATF as a handgun.  Call me at 334 - four five six - 9114 for more information.  Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  38cal .357 XTP Hornady-Critical Defense Ammo (100 rounds)
location: NW OKC, Edmond, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent: This ammo is almost impossible to find pre-loaded right now. XTP pistol bullets continue to set the standard as the bullet of choice for hunters and law enforcement officers who understand the value of a pistol bullet which will perform over a wide range of handgun velocities. Most pistol bullets are designed to work only at a factory specified velocity and a specific range. At these predetermined specifications, the bullets work just fine. But when bullet velocity begins to change, surprises can happen. Many factors cause velocities to change-gun type, barrel length, distance to target, barriers and more. That's why you need a bullet that you can depend on to perform over a wide range of velocities. You need the XTP.
